@oldblack15 
Do you know why life is able to survive on earth? The atmosphere is the building block of all life because life cannot survive without the atmosphere. Humans, and nearly all life on earth specifically, developed under conditions where we need a specific temperature range in order to survive. Now earth retains its temperature because of the atmosphere, and two main compounds are responsible for our temperature. CO2, and water vapor. Water vapor in the atmosphere hasn’t changed significantly, and all evidence we have suggests that a glacial climate on earth has a 200 ppm CO2 concentration, while an interglacial CO2 concentration had about 280-300 ppm. 

Our CO2 concentration today, is 427 ppm. That is an unprecedented concentration in observable history. When the difference between an ice age and a climate that allows tropics to thrive is just 80 ppm of CO2 concentrations, it is a massive problem that we are 120 ppm above what is healthy for tropics to thrive.

